  id: Biceps_brachii_muscle.L
  partName: Biceps brachii muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - 'The biceps brachii muscles are located along the cranial portion of both forelimbs.
    Originating from the supraglenoid tubercle of the scapula and inserting onto
    the radius and ulna, they function to flex the elbow and extend the shoulder
    joint. '
  - These muscles support forelimb propulsion, posture, and stability during locomotion.
    Their tendons traverse the shoulder joint, providing additional stabilization.
    Injury or inflammation can cause weakness, pain, and impaired forelimb performance.
